\description{
Reaction formulas are reconstructed from the GEM stoichiometric matrix using
formal metabolite names and compartments. GPR rules and participating genes are
reported explicitly. Condition-by-cell-type evidence distinguishes reactions
whose integrated gene support was actively modified by ATAC-derived regulation
(\code{RNA+ATAC}) from reactions supported by RNA without an active ATAC
contribution (\code{RNA-only}).
}
\details{
\code{RNA+ATAC} is assigned only when at least one GPR gene has finite integrated
multiome support that differs from its RNA support by more than
\code{evidence_tolerance} in the relevant condition and cell type. A non-zero
ATAC modifier is also reported separately, because a modifier can be present
without changing zero-preserving gene support.

Selecting a gene identifies every scored reaction in which that gene participates
in the GPR. The complete Boolean GPR rule is retained so that membership is not
misinterpreted as enzyme sufficiency.
}
